HEADWORD: Mythologue
<hw>Myth"o*logue</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Mythology</er>.]</ety> <def>A fabulous narrative; a myth.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>May we not . . . consider his history of the fall as an excellent
<qex>mythologue</qex>, to account for the origin of human evil?</q>
<rj><qau>Geddes.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mythology</ent>⟦br⟧
